description:
Non material minor amendment of planning permission reference P110506 dated 30 June 2011, which granted: 'Variation of condition 13 (renewable energy) of planning permission P070753, granted on appeal APP/V5570/A/08/2062599/NWF dated 22 October 2008  for demolition of existing buildings and erection of a six storey building (plus basement and rooftop enclosure) to provide for two A1/A2/A3 units (961 square metres) at part basement and ground floor and 8,021 square metres of B1 floorspace at part basement, ground and wholly to upper floors; cycle storage; green roof and associated works.â€™
The minor amendments sought are:
A]	altered articulation of the building facades;
B]	removal of revolving door at office entrance and provision of a box glazed entrance feature;
C]	addition of a glass canopy over office entrance fronting York Way;
D]	reconfiguration of layouts of the access cores (all floors) to reposition stair cores and lift locations, as well as remove one passenger lift to result in 3 passenger lifts rather than 4;
E]	clarification of maintenance access and amenity access to roof terraces; and
F]	swapped location of loading and refuse bays including associated relocated crossover point on Crinan Street and relocation of cycle parking from basement to ground floor level.
